00:00:09.777 --> 00:00:11.378 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA]
Before I was reincarnated,

00:00:11.513 --> 00:00:14.314 position:13% line:83% align:start
I was a miserable salaryman
at a toxic company.

00:00:14.448 --> 00:00:15.817 position:16% line:89% align:start
Now I'm in a crazy world

00:00:15.950 --> 00:00:18.218 position:7% line:83% align:start
where everything's an item drop
from monsters.

00:00:18.352 --> 00:00:20.454 position:27% line:83% align:start
In this new life,
I'm stuck at level one.

00:00:20.588 --> 00:00:23.223 position:27% line:83% align:start
But lucky for me,
my unique skill has maxed out

00:00:23.357 --> 00:00:25.560 position:10% line:89% align:start
all my drop stats to rank S.

00:00:25.927 --> 00:00:27.929 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, today is moving day again!

00:00:28.061 --> 00:00:30.097 position:10% line:89% align:start
And yes, that is a metal me!

00:00:30.230 --> 00:00:31.431 position:27% line:89% align:start
Because why not?

00:00:31.566 --> 00:00:33.400 position:7% line:89% align:start
Hold on. Is that another girl?

00:00:33.535 --> 00:00:35.269 position:21% line:83% align:start
Not that I'm against
making new friends.

00:00:35.402 --> 00:00:37.772 position:16% line:83% align:start
I just never know what's
gonna happen out here!

00:02:07.829 --> 00:02:09.864 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:02:16.604 --> 00:02:18.039 position:41% line:89% align:start
[yawns]

00:02:18.171 --> 00:02:20.575 position:38% line:89% align:start
[chewing]

00:02:20.942 --> 00:02:21.943 position:30% line:89% align:start
Hi there, Yota!

00:02:22.076 --> 00:02:23.711 position:33% line:89% align:start
Good morning!

00:02:23.845 --> 00:02:25.245 position:33% line:89% align:start
Good morning!

00:02:25.847 --> 00:02:26.514 position:35% line:89% align:start
Um. [gasps]

00:02:26.648 --> 00:02:29.182 position:19% line:89% align:start
Celeste? What happened?

00:02:29.817 --> 00:02:30.718 position:33% line:89% align:start
Good morning.

00:02:30.852 --> 00:02:33.220 position:38% line:83% align:start
She said
that her head was hurting.

00:02:33.353 --> 00:02:34.354 position:41% line:89% align:start
Really?

00:02:34.488 --> 00:02:35.757 position:7% line:89% align:start
Do you think you caught a cold?

00:02:35.890 --> 00:02:37.025 position:41% line:89% align:start
Oh, no.

00:02:37.157 --> 00:02:38.492 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's from the magic storm.

00:02:38.626 --> 00:02:40.360 position:5% line:89% align:start
I remember learning about those.

00:02:40.494 --> 00:02:41.896 position:10% line:89% align:start
That's the natural phenomenon

00:02:42.030 --> 00:02:43.965 position:21% line:83% align:start
that prevents people
from using magic, isn't it?

00:02:44.464 --> 00:02:46.034 position:33% line:83% align:start
I always get
these throbbing headaches

00:02:46.166 --> 00:02:49.037 position:19% line:83% align:start
and my head feels like
it's filled with metal boulders.

00:02:49.169 --> 00:02:50.672 position:16% line:89% align:start
Aw, man, I didn't realize

00:02:50.805 --> 00:02:53.173 position:13% line:83% align:start
the storms had those kinds
of side effects, too.

00:02:53.574 --> 00:02:55.943 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'll be fine as long
as I don't let it keep me down.

00:02:56.077 --> 00:02:58.412 position:19% line:83% align:start
After the storm passes,
I'll feel much better.

00:02:58.546 --> 00:02:59.881 position:30% line:89% align:start
I have an idea!

00:03:00.014 --> 00:03:01.716 position:21% line:83% align:start
Instead of going back
to the dungeon today,

00:03:01.849 --> 00:03:03.483 position:21% line:83% align:start
why don't we go look
at bigger houses?

00:03:03.885 --> 00:03:05.820 position:24% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA] Hopefully,
we can find one big enough

00:03:05.953 --> 00:03:08.221 position:16% line:83% align:start
that she won't feel sick
during magic storms.

00:03:08.355 --> 00:03:12.359 position:5% line:83% align:start
Maybe there are even houses that
are built to counteract them.

00:03:13.161 --> 00:03:15.495 position:7% line:89% align:start
Well, I hope you folks like it.

00:03:15.630 --> 00:03:16.864 position:30% line:83% align:start
I'm pretty sure
this is the only one

00:03:16.998 --> 00:03:20.300 position:27% line:83% align:start
I have that meets
all of your requirements.

00:03:22.036 --> 00:03:23.104 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:03:23.236 --> 00:03:24.138 position:33% line:89% align:start
My headache!

00:03:24.271 --> 00:03:25.405 position:27% line:89% align:start
It's cleared up!

00:03:25.540 --> 00:03:26.741 position:24% line:89% align:start
That's great news!

00:03:26.874 --> 00:03:28.910 position:21% line:83% align:start
Yes! I didn't realize
there were houses

00:03:29.043 --> 00:03:30.243 position:13% line:89% align:start
that could help with that!

00:03:30.377 --> 00:03:31.478 position:16% line:83% align:start
Then you're going to love
this property

00:03:31.612 --> 00:03:32.914 position:24% line:89% align:start
since it was built

00:03:33.047 --> 00:03:34.782 position:21% line:83% align:start
using the very latest
magic storm-blocking

00:03:34.916 --> 00:03:35.950 position:21% line:89% align:start
construction methods.

00:03:36.084 --> 00:03:37.952 position:13% line:83% align:start
I imagine that should feel
quite reassuring

00:03:38.086 --> 00:03:39.219 position:24% line:89% align:start
for any magic user.

00:03:39.352 --> 00:03:40.888 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:03:41.789 --> 00:03:44.158 position:10% line:83% align:start
The kitchen is its own room,
and it's so big!

00:03:44.291 --> 00:03:45.827 position:16% line:89% align:start
What do you think so far?

00:03:45.960 --> 00:03:47.360 position:35% line:89% align:start
I love it!

00:03:47.494 --> 00:03:48.896 position:33% line:83% align:start
So, what are
the monthly payments

00:03:49.030 --> 00:03:49.964 position:33% line:89% align:start
looking like?

00:03:50.098 --> 00:03:51.298 position:13% line:89% align:start
Given the modern technology

00:03:51.431 --> 00:03:52.900 position:38% line:83% align:start
that went
into this home's construction,

00:03:53.034 --> 00:03:56.170 position:19% line:83% align:start
it's listed for higher
than the usual market price.

00:03:56.303 --> 00:03:58.139 position:30% line:89% align:start
400,000 pilos.

00:03:58.271 --> 00:04:00.041 position:27% line:83% align:start
[EMILY, CELESTE]
400,000 pilos?

00:04:00.174 --> 00:04:01.475 position:24% line:89% align:start
Sounds reasonable.

00:04:01.609 --> 00:04:02.977 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Thanks, we'll take it.
-[gasps]

00:04:03.111 --> 00:04:05.079 position:5% line:89% align:start
Ryota, let's think this through.

00:04:05.213 --> 00:04:06.379 position:21% line:89% align:start
There're more, right?

00:04:06.514 --> 00:04:07.815 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA]
I'm sold.

00:04:07.949 --> 00:04:09.282 position:30% line:83% align:start
I want a place
where you and Emily will wake up

00:04:09.416 --> 00:04:10.818 position:24% line:89% align:start
smiling every day.

00:04:10.952 --> 00:04:13.554 position:16% line:83% align:start
That was at the very top
of my list of new-home criteria.

00:04:13.688 --> 00:04:14.956 position:44% line:83% align:start
[EVE]
Rabbit.

00:04:15.089 --> 00:04:16.958 position:24% line:83% align:start
Besides, when I saw
how much better you felt

00:04:17.091 --> 00:04:18.492 position:21% line:89% align:start
just walking in here,

00:04:18.626 --> 00:04:21.729 position:24% line:83% align:start
I wasn't interested
in looking at any other options.

00:04:22.163 --> 00:04:23.296 position:35% line:89% align:start
I'm ready!

00:04:23.430 --> 00:04:25.233 position:30% line:89% align:start
Let's move in!

00:04:25.365 --> 00:04:27.635 position:27% line:89% align:start
[birds chirping]

00:04:31.806 --> 00:04:34.441 position:21% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA] It seems like
the magic storm is finally over.

00:04:34.575 --> 00:04:36.611 position:21% line:89% align:start
Yes, and look around.

00:04:36.744 --> 00:04:39.046 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:04:43.050 --> 00:04:44.185 position:38% line:89% align:start
Goodness.

00:04:44.351 --> 00:04:46.486 position:35% line:83% align:start
That Emily,
she did this in one day?

00:04:46.621 --> 00:04:47.855 position:30% line:89% align:start
Amazing right?

00:04:47.989 --> 00:04:49.724 position:16% line:89% align:start
I just can't get over it.

00:04:49.857 --> 00:04:51.259 position:10% line:89% align:start
By the way, what's our plan?

00:04:51.391 --> 00:04:52.760 position:44% line:83% align:start
[EVE]
Carrot! [grunts]

00:04:52.894 --> 00:04:54.796 position:7% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA] The harvest festival's
coming up soon.

00:04:54.929 --> 00:04:56.631 position:19% line:83% align:start
I think we should look
at Erza's list

00:04:56.764 --> 00:04:59.366 position:13% line:83% align:start
and then try to track down
the high-priced items on it.

00:04:59.499 --> 00:05:00.835 position:33% line:83% align:start
We need to be
thoroughly prepared

00:05:00.968 --> 00:05:03.436 position:13% line:83% align:start
to handle the rare monsters
on level seven.

00:05:03.871 --> 00:05:05.006 position:33% line:89% align:start
Carrots, too?

00:05:05.139 --> 00:05:06.439 position:35% line:89% align:start
Of course!

00:05:06.574 --> 00:05:08.543 position:16% line:83% align:start
We can get a few carrots
while we're out there!

00:05:09.744 --> 00:05:10.611 position:38% line:89% align:start
Forgiven!

00:05:11.012 --> 00:05:13.181 position:24% line:83% align:start
Hope you're hungry,
'cause I got breakfast!

00:05:13.313 --> 00:05:14.749 position:41% line:89% align:start
Sweet!

00:05:14.882 --> 00:05:16.784 position:16% line:83% align:start
A delicious, healthy meal
is exactly what we all need

00:05:16.918 --> 00:05:19.120 position:5% line:83% align:start
-before we head out there today!
-Thank you.

00:05:19.253 --> 00:05:20.353 position:35% line:89% align:start
Absolutely!

00:05:20.487 --> 00:05:22.757 position:41% line:89% align:start
Carrot!

00:05:26.294 --> 00:05:27.228 position:44% line:89% align:start
Snow?

00:05:27.360 --> 00:05:29.130 position:13% line:89% align:start
On the inside of a dungeon?

00:05:29.263 --> 00:05:30.631 position:16% line:89% align:start
It's called dungeon snow.

00:05:30.765 --> 00:05:32.200 position:38% line:83% align:start
Depending
on how they're created,

00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:34.902 position:10% line:83% align:start
some dungeons do have floors
that simulate winter.

00:05:35.036 --> 00:05:36.336 position:24% line:89% align:start
That's incredible.

00:05:39.040 --> 00:05:40.074 position:16% line:89% align:start
You've got all the info.

00:05:40.208 --> 00:05:41.374 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm impressed.

00:05:41.509 --> 00:05:44.011 position:19% line:83% align:start
Oh, I wouldn't take it
to that extreme.

00:05:44.145 --> 00:05:45.680 position:16% line:89% align:start
Impressed? He praised me!

00:05:45.813 --> 00:05:48.816 position:19% line:89% align:start
[footsteps approaching]

00:05:49.617 --> 00:05:51.418 position:24% line:89% align:start
[CELESTE chuckling]

00:05:52.820 --> 00:05:53.420 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:05:53.554 --> 00:05:54.956 position:30% line:89% align:start
[both groaning]

00:05:55.089 --> 00:05:56.489 position:24% line:89% align:start
Well done, you two!

00:05:56.624 --> 00:05:59.994 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm so proud of you
I can hardly contain myself!

00:06:00.493 --> 00:06:01.461 position:41% line:83% align:start
[BOTH]
Captain.

00:06:01.596 --> 00:06:03.264 position:13% line:89% align:start
That was quite a challenge

00:06:03.396 --> 00:06:04.765 position:16% line:89% align:start
and you suffered so much!

00:06:04.899 --> 00:06:06.634 position:5% line:89% align:start
Believe me, I know how you feel!

00:06:06.767 --> 00:06:09.469 position:7% line:89% align:start
[sighs] I mean that literally.

00:06:09.604 --> 00:06:12.073 position:24% line:83% align:start
Because every time
either of you felt pain,

00:06:12.206 --> 00:06:14.609 position:30% line:83% align:start
I couldn't help
feeling it along with you!

00:06:14.742 --> 00:06:16.878 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'm so sorry you were suffering,
Captain!

00:06:17.011 --> 00:06:19.213 position:16% line:83% align:start
Don't feel sorry for me!
I don't matter!

00:06:19.347 --> 00:06:21.649 position:30% line:83% align:start
You're stronger
thanks to what you went through,

00:06:21.782 --> 00:06:24.151 position:19% line:83% align:start
and I wouldn't wish it
any other way!

00:06:24.285 --> 00:06:25.786 position:16% line:89% align:start
Get in here, both of you!

00:06:25.920 --> 00:06:27.722 position:19% line:83% align:start
[MALE PARTY MEMBER 2A]
Captain! [weeping]

00:06:27.855 --> 00:06:29.056 position:21% line:89% align:start
We feel the same way!

00:06:29.190 --> 00:06:30.390 position:16% line:83% align:start
[FEMALE PARTY MEMBER 2A]
We're so glad

00:06:30.524 --> 00:06:31.726 position:7% line:89% align:start
we were able to learn from you!

00:06:31.859 --> 00:06:34.095 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA]
And brainwashing, complete.

00:06:34.528 --> 00:06:35.663 position:33% line:89% align:start
Are you okay?

00:06:35.796 --> 00:06:37.999 position:24% line:89% align:start
Uh? Yeah! Totally.

00:06:39.200 --> 00:06:41.302 position:10% line:89% align:start
Hm. [gasps] Look over there!

00:06:41.434 --> 00:06:42.670 position:21% line:89% align:start
A monster is coming!

00:06:42.803 --> 00:06:45.806 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:06:45.940 --> 00:06:47.008 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gunshots]

00:06:48.042 --> 00:06:49.744 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[gasps]
-[grunts]

00:06:50.845 --> 00:06:51.913 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[thuds]
-[RYOTA grunts]

00:06:52.412 --> 00:06:54.982 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gunshots]

00:06:55.116 --> 00:06:55.750 position:35% line:89% align:start
[jiggling]

00:06:55.883 --> 00:06:57.652 position:16% line:89% align:start
What's going on? [grunts]

00:06:57.785 --> 00:06:59.419 position:16% line:89% align:start
Ryota, please pull back!

00:06:59.553 --> 00:07:02.256 position:13% line:83% align:start
You won't be able to defeat
that type of slime on your own!

00:07:02.390 --> 00:07:03.691 position:27% line:89% align:start
What do you mean?

00:07:03.824 --> 00:07:05.393 position:35% line:83% align:start
Guts slimes
become selectively invincible

00:07:05.526 --> 00:07:07.028 position:16% line:89% align:start
when they're near death.

00:07:07.161 --> 00:07:09.462 position:19% line:83% align:start
They won't take damage
from the last person to attack.

00:07:09.597 --> 00:07:10.865 position:19% line:89% align:start
You can't hurt it now.

00:07:10.998 --> 00:07:12.465 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA]
So we need someone to weaken it

00:07:12.600 --> 00:07:14.035 position:10% line:89% align:start
and someone to finish it off.

00:07:14.168 --> 00:07:15.703 position:30% line:89% align:start
Right. [shouts]

00:07:15.836 --> 00:07:18.471 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[fire blazing]
-[sparkling]

00:07:19.373 --> 00:07:21.409 position:10% line:89% align:start
Oh, wow! You totally beat it!

00:07:21.542 --> 00:07:23.311 position:16% line:89% align:start
This floor is solo-proof.

00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:24.679 position:27% line:89% align:start
Not very common.

00:07:25.046 --> 00:07:27.515 position:27% line:83% align:start
We should switch
our attack order going forward.

00:07:27.648 --> 00:07:28.683 position:27% line:89% align:start
Ryota, hold back.

00:07:28.816 --> 00:07:30.151 position:16% line:89% align:start
You can finish them off.

00:07:33.654 --> 00:07:34.956 position:35% line:89% align:start
[shouting]

00:07:35.089 --> 00:07:36.090 position:41% line:89% align:start
[thuds]

00:07:36.857 --> 00:07:38.326 position:21% line:89% align:start
Okay, it's yours now!

00:07:38.726 --> 00:07:41.461 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[gunshot]
-[sparkling]

00:07:41.595 --> 00:07:43.831 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Amazing! We did it!
-Yup.

00:07:43.965 --> 00:07:45.465 position:33% line:83% align:start
It turns out
they're not that strong

00:07:45.599 --> 00:07:47.068 position:7% line:89% align:start
if we're all fighting together.

00:07:47.467 --> 00:07:48.736 position:41% line:89% align:start
Onions.

00:07:48.869 --> 00:07:50.738 position:24% line:83% align:start
What's the matter,
you don't like onions?

00:07:50.871 --> 00:07:52.406 position:19% line:89% align:start
All I need are carrots.

00:07:52.540 --> 00:07:55.475 position:7% line:83% align:start
In that case, I can make curry
for dinner tonight.

00:07:55.609 --> 00:07:57.044 position:7% line:89% align:start
It'll have potatoes and onions,

00:07:57.178 --> 00:08:00.081 position:16% line:83% align:start
and big chunks of carrots
just for you, Eve!

00:08:00.214 --> 00:08:01.549 position:19% line:89% align:start
Yay, big carrot chunks!

00:08:01.682 --> 00:08:03.718 position:13% line:89% align:start
[laughs] Sounds good to me!

00:08:03.851 --> 00:08:05.353 position:13% line:83% align:start
What do you think, Celeste?
Curry?

00:08:05.485 --> 00:08:06.988 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Watch out!
-[yelps]

00:08:07.421 --> 00:08:08.289 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[thuds]
-[yelps]

00:08:08.422 --> 00:08:10.157 position:35% line:83% align:start
-No! Yota!
-Carrots!

00:08:10.658 --> 00:08:11.993 position:33% line:89% align:start
I'll be okay.

00:08:12.126 --> 00:08:14.328 position:19% line:83% align:start
Please call me anything
other than carrots!

00:08:14.462 --> 00:08:16.597 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's not like the other ones
we've been fighting.

00:08:16.731 --> 00:08:18.165 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA]
Got to be rare.

00:08:18.799 --> 00:08:21.502 position:7% line:83% align:start
Celeste, what do we have to do
to beat this one?

00:08:21.635 --> 00:08:23.037 position:16% line:89% align:start
That's a high guts slime.

00:08:23.170 --> 00:08:25.039 position:19% line:83% align:start
It still needs someone
to finish it off

00:08:25.172 --> 00:08:26.340 position:24% line:89% align:start
like the other one,

00:08:26.474 --> 00:08:27.942 position:7% line:83% align:start
but when it's in its invincible
near-death state,

00:08:28.075 --> 00:08:30.211 position:13% line:83% align:start
it will reflect all attacks
used against it.

00:08:30.344 --> 00:08:31.779 position:24% line:89% align:start
Keep that in mind.

00:08:31.912 --> 00:08:34.348 position:10% line:83% align:start
We'll have to be more careful
with it than usual.

00:08:34.482 --> 00:08:36.517 position:19% line:89% align:start
Let me. I know its HP.

00:08:36.650 --> 00:08:37.918 position:27% line:89% align:start
I want to do it.

00:08:38.052 --> 00:08:39.220 position:27% line:89% align:start
Are you serious?

00:08:39.353 --> 00:08:40.821 position:10% line:89% align:start
I killed one of them before.

00:08:40.955 --> 00:08:42.957 position:16% line:89% align:start
It was about this strong!

00:08:43.090 --> 00:08:44.025 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:08:45.826 --> 00:08:47.728 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Get him, Carrots!
-Right!

00:08:47.862 --> 00:08:51.032 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[gunshot]
-[sparkling]

