00:08:56.771 --> 00:08:58.806 position:10% line:89% align:start
Heck, yeah. That's teamwork!

00:08:58.939 --> 00:09:01.308 position:24% line:83% align:start
The jewel it drops
is very useful.

00:09:01.442 --> 00:09:02.643 position:24% line:89% align:start
When it's equipped,

00:09:02.777 --> 00:09:03.644 position:30% line:83% align:start
it can reflect
some attacks received

00:09:03.778 --> 00:09:05.012 position:24% line:89% align:start
back onto enemies.

00:09:05.146 --> 00:09:07.248 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA]
Wow. That sounds pretty cool.

00:09:07.381 --> 00:09:08.282 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:09:08.416 --> 00:09:09.984 position:35% line:89% align:start
[jiggling]

00:09:10.117 --> 00:09:11.952 position:27% line:83% align:start
It is reflecting
the slime's attacks,

00:09:12.086 --> 00:09:13.921 position:33% line:83% align:start
but not much
seems to be happening.

00:09:14.055 --> 00:09:16.824 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-[sparkling]

00:09:16.957 --> 00:09:18.292 position:44% line:83% align:start
[EVE]
Carrot!

00:09:18.426 --> 00:09:20.428 position:16% line:83% align:start
You defeated the monster
just by standing there!

00:09:20.561 --> 00:09:23.764 position:30% line:83% align:start
Yes. It reduces
the effort involved, at least.

00:09:23.898 --> 00:09:25.099 position:27% line:89% align:start
It's a lot faster

00:09:25.232 --> 00:09:26.834 position:10% line:83% align:start
when I attack things myself,
though.

00:09:26.967 --> 00:09:29.236 position:16% line:83% align:start
[EVE] Low-Level's carrots
are the bestest ever!

00:09:29.870 --> 00:09:31.238 position:30% line:83% align:start
I'll just stick
with the original plan

00:09:31.372 --> 00:09:33.808 position:13% line:83% align:start
and sell this thing to Erza
when we get home.

00:09:37.144 --> 00:09:40.448 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:09:40.881 --> 00:09:43.451 position:21% line:83% align:start
This is the rare drop
from Telulu level seven!

00:09:43.584 --> 00:09:44.752 position:24% line:89% align:start
It's a Slime Tear!

00:09:44.885 --> 00:09:46.521 position:16% line:89% align:start
Did she say level seven?

00:09:46.654 --> 00:09:48.422 position:7% line:89% align:start
Yeah, you know, the guts stuff.

00:09:48.557 --> 00:09:50.091 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's right.

00:09:50.224 --> 00:09:51.592 position:13% line:83% align:start
So, you're still interested
in buying it off me, right?

00:09:51.725 --> 00:09:54.228 position:5% line:89% align:start
Yes. Just like we agreed before.

00:09:54.628 --> 00:09:55.930 position:41% line:89% align:start
Thanks!

00:09:56.063 --> 00:09:57.098 position:7% line:83% align:start
My shop's rank and trust level
will go up again

00:09:57.231 --> 00:09:59.333 position:27% line:83% align:start
after I add this
to our inventory.

00:09:59.467 --> 00:10:00.868 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'm just glad I could be of use.

00:10:01.001 --> 00:10:02.169 position:41% line:83% align:start
[ERZA]
Always!

00:10:02.303 --> 00:10:03.637 position:35% line:83% align:start
And here's
the three million pilos

00:10:03.771 --> 00:10:04.972 position:19% line:89% align:start
for this item's worth!

00:10:05.106 --> 00:10:06.240 position:19% line:83% align:start
-[EMILY, CELESTE gasps]
-That much?

00:10:06.373 --> 00:10:08.042 position:16% line:83% align:start
The price is a bit higher
right now.

00:10:08.175 --> 00:10:10.444 position:7% line:83% align:start
But that's because it's almost
harvest festival time.

00:10:10.579 --> 00:10:12.246 position:19% line:89% align:start
[EMILY, CELESTE giggle]

00:10:16.617 --> 00:10:18.719 position:19% line:89% align:start
[RYOTA FAMILY chuckle]

00:10:21.722 --> 00:10:24.658 position:30% line:83% align:start
Um, excuse me.
I'd like to join a party!

00:10:27.995 --> 00:10:29.463 position:19% line:89% align:start
Can I join you, please?

00:10:29.598 --> 00:10:31.765 position:38% line:83% align:start
Join us?
Aren't you a little young?

00:10:31.899 --> 00:10:34.001 position:30% line:89% align:start
[chuckles] Ah!

00:10:35.836 --> 00:10:36.937 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:10:37.338 --> 00:10:40.274 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:10:40.407 --> 00:10:41.342 position:19% line:89% align:start
[SKELETON 6A chuckles]

00:10:45.880 --> 00:10:47.715 position:21% line:83% align:start
-[SKELETON 6A growls]
-[grunts]

00:10:49.584 --> 00:10:51.051 position:27% line:89% align:start
[grunts] Oh, man.

00:10:51.185 --> 00:10:53.387 position:24% line:83% align:start
The red skeleton is
three times faster than normal!

00:10:53.522 --> 00:10:54.722 position:30% line:89% align:start
Doesn't matter.

00:10:56.056 --> 00:10:58.959 position:21% line:83% align:start
-[SKELETON 6A grunts]
-Because I'm still way faster.

00:11:01.428 --> 00:11:04.665 position:24% line:83% align:start
[DUNGEON VOICE 1A]
Ryota's max MP increased by one.

00:11:04.798 --> 00:11:06.568 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA]
Wait, my MP?

00:11:06.700 --> 00:11:08.235 position:24% line:89% align:start
Like Magic Points?

00:11:08.369 --> 00:11:11.038 position:19% line:83% align:start
So that means the drops
on the fifth floor increase it?

00:11:11.172 --> 00:11:12.673 position:19% line:83% align:start
And since I didn't have
any before,

00:11:12.806 --> 00:11:14.842 position:19% line:83% align:start
I now have the ability
to use magic!

00:11:14.975 --> 00:11:17.811 position:33% line:83% align:start
How do you go
about learning magic, anyway?

00:11:20.981 --> 00:11:23.150 position:10% line:89% align:start
Exactly three million pilos.

00:11:23.284 --> 00:11:25.520 position:10% line:83% align:start
-I can't believe I bought it.
-I'm sorry.

00:11:25.654 --> 00:11:26.987 position:5% line:89% align:start
Look, I know it's a big expense,

00:11:27.121 --> 00:11:29.323 position:5% line:83% align:start
but people generally learn magic
by leveling up,

00:11:29.456 --> 00:11:32.326 position:10% line:83% align:start
and doing so is off the table
for you, unfortunately.

00:11:32.860 --> 00:11:35.896 position:30% line:83% align:start
So, you can eat
this magic fruit instead

00:11:36.030 --> 00:11:38.432 position:24% line:83% align:start
and instantly learn
a random magic spell.

00:11:38.866 --> 00:11:40.901 position:16% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA] I've never heard
of anything like that.

00:11:41.035 --> 00:11:43.170 position:27% line:83% align:start
You should eat it
and see what happens!

00:11:43.304 --> 00:11:44.639 position:27% line:89% align:start
No. Not just yet.

00:11:45.139 --> 00:11:47.908 position:13% line:83% align:start
There's a reason I decided
to go outside of town for this.

00:11:48.510 --> 00:11:50.778 position:5% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA] The odds of this working
are 50-50,

00:11:50.911 --> 00:11:53.180 position:10% line:89% align:start
but still, I want to try it.

00:11:53.314 --> 00:11:54.215 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:11:54.882 --> 00:11:56.250 position:41% line:89% align:start
[poofs]

00:11:56.984 --> 00:11:58.553 position:33% line:89% align:start
I get it now.

00:11:58.687 --> 00:12:00.988 position:13% line:83% align:start
You let it become a stray,
so it'll drop something better.

00:12:01.121 --> 00:12:03.724 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:12:03.857 --> 00:12:06.193 position:35% line:89% align:start
[jiggling]

00:12:07.161 --> 00:12:08.697 position:21% line:89% align:start
[gasps] Is that you?

00:12:08.829 --> 00:12:11.165 position:41% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA]
Hey, neat! It's a Metal Ryota!

00:12:12.967 --> 00:12:14.068 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[thuds]
-[grunts]

00:12:15.236 --> 00:12:17.338 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[grunts]
-[gun cocking]

00:12:18.305 --> 00:12:20.374 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gunshots]

00:12:20.508 --> 00:12:23.410 position:21% line:83% align:start
It's tough! And fast!
And super strong!

00:12:23.545 --> 00:12:24.979 position:21% line:89% align:start
My best guess is that

00:12:25.112 --> 00:12:27.848 position:10% line:83% align:start
it takes on 80% of the specs
of whatever it copies.

00:12:28.282 --> 00:12:30.351 position:21% line:83% align:start
Not a monster suited
for big gatherings.

00:12:30.484 --> 00:12:31.852 position:24% line:89% align:start
[gasps and grunts]

00:12:33.688 --> 00:12:34.556 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gunshot]

00:12:34.689 --> 00:12:36.991 position:35% line:89% align:start
[sparkling]

00:12:37.758 --> 00:12:38.959 position:41% line:89% align:start
[thuds]

00:12:39.093 --> 00:12:40.995 position:7% line:89% align:start
It's the same fruit as before.

00:12:41.128 --> 00:12:43.097 position:10% line:89% align:start
No, it's actually different.

00:12:44.666 --> 00:12:46.433 position:16% line:89% align:start
I see. Could this mean...

00:12:46.568 --> 00:12:49.870 position:7% line:83% align:start
Yeah. Here, let's test it out.
[chomps]

00:12:52.339 --> 00:12:53.307 position:30% line:89% align:start
Okay, hold on.

00:12:53.440 --> 00:12:54.875 position:27% line:83% align:start
What do you mean
you've learned magic?

00:12:55.009 --> 00:12:56.844 position:7% line:89% align:start
You really learned two spells?

00:12:56.977 --> 00:12:59.380 position:5% line:89% align:start
Yeah. One is called Wind Cutter.

00:12:59.514 --> 00:13:02.082 position:13% line:83% align:start
[CELESTE] It's a level-one
wind elemental spell.

00:13:02.550 --> 00:13:03.884 position:30% line:89% align:start
That's amazing!

00:13:04.018 --> 00:13:06.186 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm dying to know
what the other spell does now!

00:13:06.320 --> 00:13:08.255 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm actually curious
about it, too!

00:13:08.389 --> 00:13:10.525 position:10% line:89% align:start
Okay, but it's kind of weird.

00:13:11.025 --> 00:13:12.694 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'll give it a try
on those guys.

00:13:13.227 --> 00:13:15.262 position:16% line:89% align:start
So, do what we always do.

00:13:15.396 --> 00:13:16.297 position:41% line:89% align:start
Got it!

00:13:16.430 --> 00:13:17.197 position:33% line:89% align:start
Easy enough!

00:13:17.331 --> 00:13:20.434 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Inferno!
-[fire blazing]

00:13:20.568 --> 00:13:21.368 position:35% line:89% align:start
[sparkling]

00:13:21.503 --> 00:13:22.369 position:38% line:89% align:start
[growls]

00:13:22.936 --> 00:13:24.539 position:27% line:89% align:start
And, Reservation!

00:13:27.742 --> 00:13:29.343 position:24% line:83% align:start
-I don't think so!
-[gunshot]

00:13:29.476 --> 00:13:31.979 position:24% line:83% align:start
-[bullet whistling]
-[grunts]

00:13:32.846 --> 00:13:34.683 position:35% line:89% align:start
[sparkling]

00:13:34.815 --> 00:13:36.150 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hey, that was cool!

00:13:36.283 --> 00:13:38.018 position:16% line:89% align:start
I feel like I'm Yota now!

00:13:38.152 --> 00:13:40.522 position:38% line:83% align:start
You mean,
what that spell does is...

00:13:40.655 --> 00:13:42.923 position:7% line:83% align:start
Yep, although I have to use it
on a monster

00:13:43.057 --> 00:13:44.592 position:19% line:89% align:start
before I even attack it

00:13:44.726 --> 00:13:47.928 position:10% line:83% align:start
and then my drop rates apply
to whomever actually defeats it.

00:13:48.395 --> 00:13:50.632 position:27% line:83% align:start
So, then it makes
someone else rank S?

00:13:50.765 --> 00:13:52.933 position:7% line:89% align:start
Yeah, but it's not that useful.

00:13:53.067 --> 00:13:54.201 position:19% line:89% align:start
It's just for monsters,

00:13:54.335 --> 00:13:55.603 position:13% line:83% align:start
so there's really not much
it can do

00:13:55.737 --> 00:13:57.404 position:13% line:83% align:start
other than help with drops
if I'm around.

00:13:57.539 --> 00:13:58.939 position:41% line:83% align:start
[EMILY]
I think it's useful!

00:13:59.073 --> 00:14:00.742 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Uh?
-[EMILY] In fact, I'm grateful!

00:14:00.874 --> 00:14:02.376 position:7% line:89% align:start
Um, what are you grateful for?

00:14:02.510 --> 00:14:04.713 position:16% line:83% align:start
Because I never would've
leveled up

00:14:04.845 --> 00:14:06.581 position:10% line:89% align:start
after that battle without it!

00:14:06.980 --> 00:14:07.881 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's true!

00:14:08.015 --> 00:14:09.183 position:16% line:89% align:start
When he uses that spell,

00:14:09.316 --> 00:14:10.585 position:38% line:83% align:start
it means
that someone else on his team

00:14:10.719 --> 00:14:12.152 position:13% line:89% align:start
can finish off the monster!

00:14:12.286 --> 00:14:14.321 position:30% line:83% align:start
You're helping
your whole team level up, Yota.

00:14:14.455 --> 00:14:15.989 position:33% line:83% align:start
I don't know
what could be better

00:14:16.123 --> 00:14:18.225 position:33% line:83% align:start
than a spell
that helps my friends!

00:14:18.727 --> 00:14:20.994 position:7% line:83% align:start
We can all share the experience
from now on.

00:14:21.128 --> 00:14:23.598 position:16% line:83% align:start
We'll level up together.
As a party!

00:14:23.732 --> 00:14:25.966 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Absolutely!
-Great!

00:14:28.570 --> 00:14:31.205 position:19% line:83% align:start
[RYOTA] I was thinking
I might head to Nihonium today.

00:14:31.606 --> 00:14:33.240 position:27% line:89% align:start
Uh? Isn't that...

00:14:33.775 --> 00:14:36.043 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Erza!
-Oh, Hi, Ryota.

00:14:36.176 --> 00:14:38.747 position:10% line:83% align:start
You're carrying a lot there.
Let me help you!

00:14:38.879 --> 00:14:40.447 position:21% line:89% align:start
Thank you. Seriously.

00:14:40.582 --> 00:14:42.950 position:27% line:83% align:start
I bought too much
and made things hard.

00:14:46.755 --> 00:14:48.889 position:21% line:83% align:start
[ERZA] Thanks again.
I appreciate the help!

00:14:49.022 --> 00:14:50.391 position:16% line:89% align:start
Well, I better get going.

00:14:50.525 --> 00:14:52.326 position:41% line:83% align:start
[ALICE]
You'll actually let me join?

00:14:52.459 --> 00:14:53.460 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:14:53.595 --> 00:14:54.495 position:47% line:89% align:start
Hm.

00:14:55.530 --> 00:14:58.265 position:7% line:83% align:start
